===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{Han compound|疒|t1=sickness|丙|ls=psc|c1=s|c2=p}} – illness. Note that {{lang|zh|丙}} also means “fire”, hence connotations of “lying feverishly in bed”.

===Etymology===
Cognate with {{och-l|怲|to worry}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}). This may be part of larger word family including {{och-l|炳|bright}} with the basic meaning of “warm; hot” ([[ibid.]]). It has also been connected with {{och-l|傷|id=1}} ({{zh-ref|Unger, 1986}}).

